---
import Base from '../../layouts/Base.astro';

const base = import.meta.env.BASE_URL;
---

<Base title="Connected Agents | Enhanced Task Completion">
  <article class="scenario">
    <div class="container">
      <a href={base} class="back">&larr; All scenarios</a>

      <header class="scenario__header">
        <span class="badge badge--primary">Agent Delegation</span>
        <h1>Connected Agents</h1>
        <p class="scenario__lead">
          The Orders Agent delegates inventory and fulfillment queries to a specialized Warehouse Agent,
          combining results from both agents into a single coherent response for the user.
        </p>
      </header>

      <!-- Screenshot -->
      <div class="scenario__screenshot">
        <img src={`${base}images/scenario-agents.png`} alt="Connected agent delegation in the Gradio chat UI" />
      </div>

      <!-- What happens -->
      <section class="scenario__section">
        <h2>What happens</h2>
        <p>When the user says <em>"I'm James Rivera. I have two pending orders — can you give me a full status update on both?"</em>, the agent:</p>

        <ol class="scenario__steps">
          <li>
            <div class="step">
              <div class="step__icon">&#x1F50D;</div>
              <div class="step__content">
                <strong>Calls <code>search_orders</code></strong>
                <p>Searches for all orders belonging to James Rivera and identifies the two pending ones.</p>
              </div>
            </div>
          </li>
          <li>
            <div class="step">
              <div class="step__icon">&#x1F4E6;</div>
              <div class="step__content">
                <strong>Calls <code>get_order</code> for each pending order</strong>
                <p>Retrieves full details for both orders, including items, quantities, and current processing status.</p>
              </div>
            </div>
          </li>
          <li>
            <div class="step">
              <div class="step__icon">&#x1F91D;</div>
              <div class="step__content">
                <strong>Delegates to Warehouse Agent</strong>
                <p>Hands off inventory and fulfillment queries to the connected Warehouse Agent for stock availability and shipping status.</p>
              </div>
            </div>
          </li>
          <li>
            <div class="step">
              <div class="step__icon">&#x1F3ED;</div>
              <div class="step__content">
                <strong>Warehouse Agent calls <code>check_stock</code> + <code>find_alternatives</code></strong>
                <p>The Warehouse Agent checks stock levels, finds an out-of-stock item, and looks up alternatives.</p>
              </div>
            </div>
          </li>
          <li>
            <div class="step">
              <div class="step__icon">&#x1F4AC;</div>
              <div class="step__content">
                <strong>Warehouse Agent asks a question — relayed to the user</strong>
                <p>The Warehouse Agent asks "Would you like a similar console or a different category?" — the Orders Agent relays this question back to the user and waits for their answer.</p>
              </div>
            </div>
          </li>
          <li>
            <div class="step">
              <div class="step__icon">&#x2705;</div>
              <div class="step__content">
                <strong>Combines results into a unified response</strong>
                <p>The Orders Agent merges data from both agents — order details, stock availability, shipping timelines, and the user's preference — into a single structured answer.</p>
              </div>
            </div>
          </li>
        </ol>
      </section>

      <!-- Why it matters -->
      <section class="scenario__section">
        <h2>Why it matters</h2>
        <div class="value-grid">
          <div class="value-card">
            <h3>Cross-agent orchestration</h3>
            <p>The Orders Agent seamlessly delegates to the Warehouse Agent without the user needing to know about the underlying architecture or switch contexts.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="value-card">
            <h3>Separation of concerns</h3>
            <p>Each agent owns its domain — orders vs. warehouse operations — keeping tool sets focused and prompts specialized for better accuracy.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="value-card">
            <h3>Scalable architecture</h3>
            <p>New specialist agents (shipping, billing, support) can be connected without modifying the primary agent's core logic or tool definitions.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </section>

      <!-- Try it -->
      <section class="scenario__section">
        <h2>Try it yourself</h2>
        <div class="try-prompt">
          <p class="try-prompt__label">Copy this prompt:</p>
          <blockquote class="try-prompt__text">
            I'm James Rivera. I have two pending orders — can you give me a full status update on both? I want to know exactly where each one is in the process, when they'll ship, and if anything is out of stock, what alternatives do I have?
          </blockquote>
        </div>
      </section>
    </div>
  </article>
</Base>

<style>
  .scenario {
    padding: var(--space-3xl) 0;
  }
  .back {
    display: inline-flex;
    align-items: center;
    gap: 4px;
    font-size: 0.85rem;
    font-weight: 500;
    color: var(--c-text-muted);
    margin-bottom: var(--space-xl);
  }
  .back:hover { color: var(--c-primary); }

  .scenario__header {
    max-width: 680px;
  }
  .scenario__header h1 {
    margin-top: var(--space-md);
  }
  .scenario__lead {
    margin-top: var(--space-lg);
    font-size: 1.1rem;
    color: var(--c-text-secondary);
    line-height: 1.7;
  }

  .scenario__screenshot {
    margin-top: var(--space-2xl);
    border: 1px solid var(--c-border);
    border-radius: var(--radius-lg);
    overflow: hidden;
    box-shadow: 0 8px 30px rgba(0,0,0,0.06);
  }
  .scenario__screenshot img {
    width: 100%;
  }

  .scenario__section {
    margin-top: var(--space-3xl);
  }
  .scenario__section h2 {
    margin-bottom: var(--space-lg);
  }
  .scenario__section > p {
    color: var(--c-text-secondary);
    margin-bottom: var(--space-lg);
  }

  .scenario__steps {
    list-style: none;
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: var(--space-md);
  }
  .step {
    display: flex;
    gap: var(--space-md);
    padding: var(--space-lg);
    background: var(--c-surface);
    border: 1px solid var(--c-border-subtle);
    border-radius: var(--radius-md);
    transition: border-color 0.2s ease;
  }
  .step:hover { border-color: var(--c-border); }
  .step__icon {
    font-size: 1.3rem;
    flex-shrink: 0;
    width: 36px;
    height: 36px;
    display: flex;
    align-items: center;
    justify-content: center;
  }
  .step__content strong {
    display: block;
    font-size: 0.95rem;
    margin-bottom: 2px;
  }
  .step__content p {
    font-size: 0.88rem;
    color: var(--c-text-secondary);
    line-height: 1.6;
  }

  .value-grid {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fit, minmax(240px, 1fr));
    gap: var(--space-lg);
  }
  .value-card {
    padding: var(--space-lg);
    background: var(--c-surface-raised);
    border: 1px solid var(--c-border-subtle);
    border-radius: var(--radius-md);
  }
  .value-card h3 {
    font-size: 0.95rem;
    margin-bottom: var(--space-xs);
  }
  .value-card p {
    font-size: 0.85rem;
    color: var(--c-text-secondary);
    line-height: 1.6;
  }

  .try-prompt {
    background: var(--c-surface);
    border: 1px solid var(--c-border);
    border-radius: var(--radius-md);
    padding: var(--space-lg);
  }
  .try-prompt__label {
    font-size: 0.82rem;
    font-weight: 600;
    color: var(--c-text-muted);
    margin-bottom: var(--space-sm);
  }
  .try-prompt__text {
    font-size: 0.95rem;
    color: var(--c-text);
    line-height: 1.65;
    border-left: 3px solid var(--c-primary);
    padding-left: var(--space-md);
    margin: 0;
  }
</style>
